rdf:Description.lla:note: In the 'Particulars of the Voyage' section, it is stated that the ship underwent repairs in Aberystwyth from the 7th March, 1878 until the 18th July, 1878, which accounts for the complete change of crew.
The previous vessel is possibly the 'Bramin' of Yarmouth.
The previous vessel is possibly the 'Gleaner' of Yarmouth.
There is a note within the record, stating that Thomas Pugh was discharged due to sickness and was sent home on board the SS Barrington with his belongings.
